My SQL - Structured Query Language

Datatypes:
text : char , varchar, Text, Blob
Number : Tinyint, Smallint, Mediumint, int, Bigint, Float, Double
Blob - Binary large Object File : Tinyblob, blob, Mediumblob, largeblob


queries :

1. show database db_name
2. create database db_name
3. drop database db_name
4. use db_name - it uses the database
5. show tables - it shows the all tables in the currrent database
6. create table table_name - it create the table 
   eg:
   create table IPL_PointsTable(
    Id(Position) Int, name varchar(30), win int , loss int, points int
   )
7. alter table table_name add new_colname  int(Datatype)
8. alter table table_name drop col_name - drops column
9. insert into table_name values(1,"Punjab Kings",5,0,10;) - passing values inside
10. select * from table_name - selecting and showing the datas
11. Conditions : Where - select * from IPL where name ="SRH"; 